Package uk.ac.manchester.spinnaker.alloc.db

SQLite database support.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DatabaseEngine.Connected
    Some code that may be run within a transaction and which will be given a new connection for the duration.
    DatabaseEngine.ConnectedWithResult<T>
    Some code that may be run within a transaction that returns a result and which will be given a new connection for the duration.
    DatabaseEngine.Transacted
    Some code that may be run within a transaction.
    DatabaseEngine.TransactedWithResult<T>
    Some code that may be run within a transaction that returns a result.
    SQLiteFlags
    Flags in SQLite that the driver doesn't name for us.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DataAccessExceptionMapper
    Handler for DataAccessException.
    DatabaseAwareBean
    A support class to make accessing the database a bit simpler.
    DatabaseEngine
    The database engine interface.
    DatabaseEngine.StatementWrapper
    Common shared code between DatabaseEngine.Query and DatabaseEngine.Update.
    Row
    A restricted form of result set.
    SQLExceptionMapper
    Handler for SQLException.
    SQLQueries
    The literal SQL queries used in this package.
    TerminationNotifyingThreadFactory
    A thread factory that makes it possible to get a notification when a thread terminates.
    UncheckedConnection
    A connection that guarantees to not throw SQLException from many of its methods.
    Utils
    Miscellaneous database-related utility operations.
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    DatabaseEngine.ArgumentCount
    If placed on a bean of type Function, specifies how many arguments that function takes.
    DatabaseEngine.Deterministic
    If placed on a bean of type Function, specifies that the function will always give the same answer with the same inputs.
    DatabaseEngine.Innocuous Deprecated.
    Consult the SQLite documentation on innocuous functions very carefully before enabling this.
